Nutri-Score is a logo which inform on the nutritional quality of food with ratings from A to E. The score take into account nutrients, food to promote (fibers, proteins, fruits, vegetables, legumes, oilseed) and to restrict (energy, saturated fatty acids, sugars, salt).

NOVA Group is a 4-groups classification to highlight level of processed food:
1 - Non processed food or minimally processed food
2 - Processed ingredients
3 - Processed food
4 - Ultra-processed food and drinks
Non processed food or minimally processed food
Eco-Score is built around similar model of Nutri-Score: it\'s a rating from A (very low impact) to E (very high impact).

This type of barcode is often used in the industry.
Code 39 is a barcode used in textile marking and drugs in pharmacies. It is also used in military sector and automotive industry.
Code 93 is a barcode used in army and automotive sectors, as well as by "Postes Canada" to encode special deliveries information.

Code 128 is a barcode often used in the industry. It is used in transport industry and for product identification in supply chains. It can also be used in automotive sector or for product marking in pharmacies. Code 128 is widely used and can also be used in many other endings.
Code ITF (Interleaved 2 of 5) is a barcode mainly used for goods shipments.
Code Codabar is a barcode designed to be read by dot matrix printers. Today, Codabar is little used for the benefit of other barcodes types, but is still used by some organisations like libraries.
Code UPC-A (Universal Product Code) is a barcode widely used in USA and Canada to identify products sold in stores and shops. It is composed of 12 digits.

Code UPC-E (Universal Product Code) is a condensed barcode of code UPC-A mainly used in USA and Canada to identify products sold in stores and shops. It is used on packaging too small to receive code UPC-A.
Code EAN-13 (European Article Numbering 13) is a barcode widely used to identify products sold in stores and shops in Europe and pretty much everywhere in the world. It is composed of 13 digits.

Code EAN-8 (European Article Numbering 8) is a condensed barcode of code EAN-13 used to identify products sold in stores and shops in Europe and pretty much everywhere in the world. It is used on packaging too small to receive code EAN-13.

"Code 93" barcode type can codify the 26 uppercase letters, the 10 digits (0 to 9) as well as the 8 special characters « -, ., space, *, $, /, +, % ». Lowercase letters and other special characters can not be codify by this barcode type.

"Code 39" barcode type can codify the 26 uppercase letters, the 10 digits (0 to 9) as well as the 7 special characters « -, ., space, $, /, +, % ». Lowercase letters and other special characters can not be codify by this barcode type.

"Codabar" barcode type can codify the 10 digits (0 to 9) as well as the 6 special characters « -, $, :, /, ., + ». It can also contain characters A, B, C or D for the first and the last barcode character to specify the beginning and the end of the string.
"ITF" barcode type must contain an even number of characters.

An API is a software library used to access a service. In the case of this application, an API is used to access a web service. This web service retrieves information from a database.\nFor example, Open Food Facts is a database of food products and provides an API to access its database. I use this API to display information on food products.
The API search function is only activated for EAN 13, EAN 8, UPC A and UPC E barcodes.
• Food products (with Open Food Facts API)
• Cosmetic products (with Open Beauty Facts API)
• Pet food products (with Open Pet Food Facts API)
• Some products may not be included in certain databases.
• There may be some errors in the information provided by the APIs.

If the \"%1$s\" option is enabled, when you scan a product barcode, a search is automatically performed on the API selected in the settings. If no information is found on the API, you can always perform a manual search on another API after the scan.

If the \"%1$s\" option is disabled, when you scan a product barcode, no information is retrieved from the remote servers. But you can always manually search for information on the scanned product. To do this, after scanning the product, click on the icon in the menu bar. You can then select an API to search.

If the product you\'re scanning is a book, you don\'t need to specify the API on which to search for information. A book\'s barcode is identifiable because it always begins with the digits \"978\". The search will automatically be performed on Open Library.

Open Food Facts is a free database about food which lists ingredients, allergens, nutritional composition and all information present on the products labels.
Open Pet Food Facts is a free database about pet food.
Open Beauty Facts is a free database about cosmetic products.
MusicBrainz is an open music encyclopedia that collects music metadata and makes it available to the public.
Open Library is a free database aimed at cataloging all published books, whatever their language.
